TITLE: Defining Index Structure in ElectroDB
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the structure for defining indexes in ElectroDB. It includes options for specifying access patterns, partition keys, sort keys, and various index properties such as collections and types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tywalch/electrodb/blob/master/www/src/pages/en/modeling/indexes.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
indexes: {
	[AccessPatternName]: {
		index?: string;
		collection?: string | string[];
		type?: 'isolated' | 'clustered';
		pk: {
			field: string;
			composite: AttributeName[];
			template?: string;
			cast?: 'string' | 'number';
			casing?: 'upper' | 'lower' | 'none';
		},
		sk?: {
			field: string;
			composite: AttributesName[];
			template?: string;
			cast?: 'string' | 'number';
			casing?: 'upper' | 'lower' | 'none';
		},
	}
}
```

