TITLE: Creating a Case-Insensitive Search Field with Hidden Attributes in ElectroDB
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to implement a hidden 'descriptionSearch' attribute that maintains a lowercase version of the 'description' field for case-insensitive filtering. The watch property ensures the search field updates whenever the description changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tywalch/electrodb/blob/master/www/src/pages/en/recipes/calculated-attribute.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
