TITLE: Chained Where Clauses with OR and AND Logic
DESCRIPTION: Example of chaining multiple where clauses with both OR and AND logic. This checks if an animal is dangerous OR hasn't been fed, AND has a birthday within the last month.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tywalch/electrodb/blob/master/www/src/pages/en/mutations/conditions.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
animals
  .update({ animal: "tiger", name: "janet" })
  .set({ keeper: "Joe Exotic" })
  .where(
    (attr, op) => `
    ${op.eq(attr.dangerous, true)} OR ${op.notExists(attr.lastFed)}
  `,
  )
  .where(({ birthday }, { between }) => {
    const today = Date.now();
    const lastMonth = today - 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 30;
    return between(birthday, lastMonth, today);
  })
  .go();
```

