TITLE: Performing Write Transactions in ElectroDB with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the transaction.write() method in ElectroDB to perform write transactions across multiple entities. It shows the basic structure of a transaction and how to commit mutations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tywalch/electrodb/blob/master/www/src/pages/en/mutations/transact-write.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
await yourService.transaction
  .write(({ entity1, entity2 }) => [
    entity1
      .create({ prop1: "value1", prop2: "value2" })
      .commit({ response: "all_old" }),

    entity2
      .update({ prop1: "value1", prop2: "value2" })
      .set({ prop3: "value3" })
      .commit({ response: "all_old" }),
  ])
  .go();
```

