TITLE: Example of Duplicate Index Definition in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how duplicate index names can be accidentally defined in an ElectroDB model, which would trigger error code 1004 for duplicate indexes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tywalch/electrodb/blob/master/www/src/pages/en/reference/errors.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
  indexes: {
    index1: {
      index: "idx1", // <-- duplicate "idx1"
      pk: {},
      sk: {}
    },
    index2: {
      index: "idx1", // <-- duplicate "idx1"
      pk: {},
      sk: {}
    }
  }
}
```

