TITLE: Primary Index vs Global Secondary Index Definition in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how ElectroDB differentiates between Primary Index and Global Secondary Index based on the presence of the 'index' property in the definition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tywalch/electrodb/blob/master/www/src/pages/en/reference/errors.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// ElectroDB interprets as the Primary Index because it lacks an `index` property.
{
  indexes: {
    myIndex: {
      pk: {
        field: "pk",
        composite: ["org"]
      },
      sk: {
        field: "sk",
        composite: ["id"]
      }
    }
  }
}
// ElectroDB interprets as a Global Secondary Index because it has an `index` property.
{
  indexes: {
    myIndex: {
      index: "gsi1"
      pk: {
        field: "gsi1pk",
        composite: ["org"]
      },
      sk: {
        field: "gsi1sk",
        composite: ["id"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

